description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Band 6 Senior Physiotherapist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Cheltenham &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;£31,365- £37,890&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 37.5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;1 x Fixed Term contract/secondment opportunity for up to 12 months*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;*Internal applicants who wish to be considered for a secondment opportunity should discuss with their line manager the suitability of a possible secondment*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you believe in person-centred care and want to make a difference?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like to develop your skills in the Community setting?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This exciting role demands excellent team working, innovation and commitment to the delivery of expert patient care within an integrated health and social care environment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a Physiotherapist with;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience across a range of specialities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ability to support patients who have a range of complex multi-pathology and long term conditions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An understanding of multidisciplinary working with the ability to take positive risk and deliver patient-centred care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication skills to network with colleagues, relevant services and partner organisations.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills to deliver high quality Physiotherapy assessment and treatment with a keen interest in developing community rehabilitation skills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Within this role you will be actively involved in staff development and training, liaising with medical staff, health care professionals, working in partnership with social services, external agencies and organisations, in addition to supporting the Professional Team Leads and Team Managers in the delivery of effective patient care. You will hold a varied caseload and have the opportunity to carry out urgent assessments (requiring same or next day response) as well as deliver long-term rehabilitation to patients with more complex conditions and those receiving reablement. You will be able to access support from and work alongside clinical specialists in a range of areas.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisting date: 18&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: 25&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or queries contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Philippa Norris-Jones or Cassie Lee, Physiotherapy Professional Leads on 0300 421 8367 Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Philippa.Norris-Jones@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or Cassie.Lee@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;or&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liz Burrow, Team Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;on 0300 421 8367 Email: Liz.Burrow@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
